{
  "texts": [
    "An ideal generative model would sample evenly from the chemical space surrounding the molecules in the training set.",
    "The observation of structural biases in the outputs of language models trained on SELFIES is at odds with this goal.",
    "I therefore sought to test whether, in addition to introducing biases in the chemical space explored by generative models, the choice of representation would also constrain their capacity for generalization.",
    "To test this hypothesis, I made use of an exhaustively explored chemical space: that of the GDB-13 database, which enumerates all ~975 million drug-like molecules containing up to 13 heavy atoms.",
    "Following an experimental design proposed previously, I trained chemical language models on small samples from GDB-13, using either SMILES or SELFIES to represent these molecules 61."
  ]
}